    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Test-driven development (TDD) writes a failing test before implementation, then adds minimal code to pass, then refactors. For agent systems, TDD applies best to deterministic layers — tool validators, policy engines, parsers — not to open-ended prompt quality, which still needs eval suites."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "What it is"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The Red-Green-Refactor cycle: (1) Red — write test describing desired behavior, see it fail; (2) Green — implement smallest change to pass; (3) Refactor — clean up without changing behavior. Tests drive design of small, testable modules in the agent stack."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# RED: test first\ndef test_tool_policy_blocks_delete_without_role():\n    policy = ToolPolicy(allowed_tools={\"search\"}, user_roles={\"viewer\"})\n    with pytest.raises(PermissionError):\n        policy.check(\"delete_file\", user_roles={\"viewer\"})\n\n# GREEN: minimal implementation\nclass ToolPolicy:\n    def check(self, tool: str, user_roles: dict) -> None:\n        if tool not in self.allowed_tools:\n            raise PermissionError(tool)\n\n# REFACTOR: clearer errors, logging, etc. — tests still pass"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Why it matters"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Agent features accumulate safety rules quickly: which tools require approval, max step count, PII redaction. TDD forces explicit expected behavior before code sprawls. Regressions are caught immediately because tests exist before the feature."
          }
        ]
      },
